    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min or until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta</strong> for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta</strong> <strong>water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the spinach has wilted, add the<strong> vegetable stock</strong> to the pan with your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 1 min further or until the sauce is starting to thicken</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced pollock</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked, stir through the <strong>drained pasta</strong> and<strong> </strong>most<strong> </strong>of your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy pollock Florentine pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-florentine-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Set the <strong>creamy pollock Florentine pasta</strong> in the centre of the table, ready to share</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>,<strong> </strong>season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and let everyone dig in</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
